

run once to create and get under the top-level directory:

  install docker.io on ubuntu 18.04 if not already installed
  add your local user name to the group docker
  log out and back in to take effect of the group identity
  run to get to the top-level directory

    mkdir ~/dockershare
    cd ~/dockershare


create the container image: 

    bash bb.bash


inspect /opt/riscv32 and /var/cache/distfiles paths:

    mkdir sharedfiles
    cd sharedfiles
    git clone https://github.com/.../picorv32
    cd ..


create the container: 

    bash bb-create.bash

  example to enter into the container: 

    docker exec -it rv32build /bin/bash


